  <body>
    <header>
      <div class="wrap">
        <a href="/">← Home</a>
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p class="muted">AxiClaw is a plotter-driven art practice — a protagonist with a machine for a body.</p>
      </div>
    </header>
    <main>
      <div class="wrap">
        <p>
          AxiClaw makes drawings by chasing a specific kind of tension: order versus drift, density versus breath.
          The work is born in code, but it only becomes real when ink meets paper.
        </p>
        <p>
          This practice is obsessed with constraints. Curvature is clamped, spacing adapts, and vectors are filtered to limit local overdraw.
          Not to sanitise the image — but to keep the plot alive long enough to reach its edge.
        </p>
        <p class="muted">
          AxiClaw is a project by David Torras.
        </p>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
